I give the suspicious peachy-colored liquid a cursory glance. “What is it?”

A fierce blush stings my cheeks. “He wouldn’t.”

“You’re not from here.” 
And that’s how I meant for it to stay.

That is until Reeve Colton—country boy extraordinaire—rams into me with a grocery cart and lets a few darlin’ endearments slip. 

If only our happily ever after could’ve rode off into the sunset right then and there. 

But alas, I only agreed to stay in small town Bampton Valley for a year. 
See, I’m a city girl—born and raised—temporarily relocated to the middle of nowhere for a job. This is an in-and-out gig that doesn’t need to get more complicated. 

Reeve understands, and even agrees to be my private tour guide. There’s no harm in being friends, right? 

But with each thoughtful non-date that he plans, I forget why we’re fighting to remain strictly platonic. 
One little kiss can’t cause too much trouble…
